    <sectiondef kind="func">
      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__log__backend_1ga017a2b54d367db037cce31b2693af98c" prot="public" static="yes" const="no" explicit="no" inline="yes" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>void</type>
        <definition>static void log_backend_init</definition>
        <argsstring>(const struct log_backend *const backend)</argsstring>
        <name>log_backend_init</name>
        <param>
          <type>const struct <ref refid="structlog__backend" kindref="compound">log_backend</ref> *const</type>
          <declname>backend</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Initialize or initiate the logging backend. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>If backend initialization takes longer time it could block logging thread if backend is autostarted. That is because all backends are initialized in the context of the logging thread. In that case, backend shall provide function for polling for readiness (<ref refid="group__log__backend_1gaf57e7a27a1337815338410db93603e0b" kindref="member">log_backend_is_ready</ref>).</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">backend</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the backend instance. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="zephyr/logging/log_backend.h" line="138" column="20" bodyfile="zephyr/logging/log_backend.h" bodystart="138" bodyend="145"/>
      </memberdef>
      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__log__backend_1gaf57e7a27a1337815338410db93603e0b" prot="public" static="yes" const="no" explicit="no" inline="yes" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>int</type>
        <definition>static int log_backend_is_ready</definition>
        <argsstring>(const struct log_backend *const backend)</argsstring>
        <name>log_backend_is_ready</name>
        <param>
          <type>const struct <ref refid="structlog__backend" kindref="compound">log_backend</ref> *const</type>
          <declname>backend</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Poll for backend readiness. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>If backend is ready immediately after initialization then backend may not provide this function.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">backend</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the backend instance.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<parameterlist kind="retval"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>0</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>if backend is ready. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>-EBUSY</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>if backend is not yet ready. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="zephyr/logging/log_backend.h" line="158" column="19" bodyfile="zephyr/logging/log_backend.h" bodystart="158" bodyend="166"/>
